First take the pasta and boil them in water..
Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Stir in the flour and cook for 1-2 minutes.
Take the pan off the heat and gradually stir in one-third of the milk. ...
Repeat this process, stirring all the time, allowing the sauce to become thick and shiny before adding more milk.
When all the milk is added bring to the boil.
Now to the white sauce, Add vegetables like broccoli,sweet corn,capsicum(Of different colours),green peas etc..&mix well.
Now add the boiled pasta to the sauce and mix well..Now let the pasta cook for 2-3 minutes..
Now add chilli flakes and oregano to pasta and give it a mix..
Now your pasta is ready.. Serve it hot and enjoy..
